Wash and dry produce.

Slice @tomato{1} into ¼-inch-thick rounds; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice @fresh mozzarella{4%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds.

Halve @ciabatta bread{2}. Drizzle cut sides with @olive oil{2%teaspoon}; season
with salt and pepper. Toast in #skillet{} until golden if desired.

Spread @mayonnaise{2%tablespoon} onto cut sides of ciabattas. Layer bottom
halves of ciabattas with seasoned tomato, @prosciutto{2%ounce}, and mozzarella.
Drizzle mozzarella with @balsamic glaze{5%teaspoon}. Close sandwiches.

Halve sandwiches on a diagonal; divide between plates and serve.